title: Ethiopia, Mythical Volcanoes (Part 1)
desc: Three tectonic plates intersect in the Horn of Africa; Erta Ale in Ethiopia houses one of the world's few lava lakes; Dallol's summit lies below sea level.
topic: Igneous & Metamorphic Petrology, Volcanism, & Hydrothermal Systems
series: On the Volcanoes of the World
